    <note type="biography">
        <p>Canadian-born opera singer. Born Marie Louise Cécile Emma Lajeunesse; adopted the stage name Albani. First sang at Covent Garden in 1872 and appeared there every season until 1896. Married Ernest Gye (1839–1926) in 1878.</p></note>
